        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 16 at 6:34PM CDT by NWS Kansas City/Pleasant Hill MO</headline>
        <description>At 634 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Kansas City Intl Arpt, moving northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lansing, Platte City, Kansas City Intl Arpt, Ferrelview, Farley, and
Hoover.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 29 between mile markers 10 and 19.
Interstate 435 between mile markers 24 and 39.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
